FBIS4-16522 "drsov074_v_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-074 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 Lithuania Government Asked for Funds To Air Russian Programs Government Asked for Funds To Air Russian Programs MK1604122094 Moscow OBSHCHAYA GAZETA in Russian No. 15/40, 15-21 Apr 94 (Signed to press 14 Apr) p 2 MK1604122094 Moscow OBSHCHAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [Unattributed report under the "From A to Z" rubric] [Text] The Lithuanian Radio and Television Company board has requested that the Lithuanian Government appropriate money to air "Ostankino" television and "Mayak" radio programs. If the "top chiefs" agree, the programs will be aired daily starting 1800. According to Gediminus Ilgunas, the company's chief, this will cost 800,000 lits or around $200,000.
